%h2
  Registration

  %p
    The ANRW 2020 will be held online during the week of July 27-31, 2020,
    and is scheduled together with the IETF-108 meeting.

  %p
    All attendees
    %b must
    register for the ANRW. Registration costs $25 USD for all attendees that are
    %b not
    also attending the IETF 108 meeting. Registration for the ANRW is free for
    those who have registered for IETF-108
    for the full week, on a day pass, or as a full-time student.
    The IETF registration fee is $50 USD for full-time students, and covers
    attendance at all IETF working groups, IRTF research groups, tutorials,
    and other sessions for the entire week, as well as the ANRW. 

  /%p
  /  %a.btn.btn-primary{ :href => "https://anrw-reg.irtf.org/anrw-reg-2020.html", :role => "button" } Register for ANRW 2020
  /  %a.btn.btn-primary{ :href => "https://registration.ietf.org/108/", :role => "button" } Register for IETF 108 (optional)


  /%p
  /  You
  /  %b do not
  /  need to register for IETF 108 in order to attend ANRW. If you do want
  /  to attend both IETF and ANRW, remember to come back here and register
  /  for ANRW after completing your IETF registration.

  %p
    A limited number of fee waivers are available to support those for whom
    the registration fee represents a genuine barrier to participation.
    Please contact the ANRW travel grants chair, Theresa Enghardt, for
    details.

  %p
    %a.btn.btn-primary{ :href => "mailto:anrw-travel-grants@irtf.org?subject=ANRW'20 fee waiver request&body=(This email should be sent by the applicant.)"} Request fee waiver

  %p
    At least one author of each accepted paper
    %b must
    register for the ANRW and present their paper.

  %p
    The ANRW will be streamed live and recorded. Participation will
    be provided using the IETF remote participation system. You can find
    information about that system on the IETF-108 meeting page.

